import React from 'react';
import AboutSeavapic from '../Assets/About/D05_transparent_white.png'
import AboutVesneapic from '../Assets/About/D06_transparent_white.png'

function About() {
    return (
        <div className='AboutPage'>
            <div className='page-border'>
                <div className='AboutTitle'>
                    About
                </div>
                <div className='TheArtist'>
                    <b>The Artist</b>
                    <p>I'm a digital artist that specialized in drawing cute stuffs. Started from drawing Pokémon fanarts for a few years. Currently using Clip Studio Paint as the software of choice.</p><br />
                    <p>Seavalanche is a name that was originally made for a Digimon Betamon in a game. It was chosen because Betamon has both ice and water attributes to it. The Seavalanche name gives off the feeling of calm but also powerful</p>
                </div>
                <div className='TheCharacters'>
                    <b>The Characters</b>
                    <div className='AboutSeava'>
                        <b>Seava</b>
                        <img className='AboutSeavapic' src={AboutSeavapic} alt='D05 - Seava Reference v1' /><br />
                        <p>A fox-like creature that uses ice elements to protect its beloved ones.
                            Has no known gender as Seava is one of its kind.
                            Has three forms that Seava can use: Child form, Normal form, and Ascended form.</p><br />

                        <p>Seava will use Normal form most of the time and can switch to child form when it wants or when it needs to preserve energy / hide its aura.
                            When the situation is dire, Seava will unleash its full power form, the Ascended form.</p><br />

                        <p>Seava has a cloth-like accessory that is formed from its ice and psychic aura.
                            In Child form, the cloth is wrapped around its left front leg, while in Normal form the cloth is left hanging using its psychic aura behind its back. It is visibly longer in Ascended form.</p><br />

                        <p>Seava can physically hit the target using the cloth. But it also has a signature move called Frost Force (ice element).
                            Frost Force: Seava lowers its surrounding temperature until it is cold enough that ice forms, then pushes all of it using its psychic power towards the target.</p><br />

                        <p>Primary elements on each forms:</p>
                        <ul><li>Child form has ice and water elements.</li>
                            <li>Normal form has ice and psychic elements.</li>
                            <li>Ascended form has ice and fairy elements.</li></ul><br />

                        <p>But all forms can use any of the water, ice, psychic, normal, and fairy elements moves.</p>
                        <br /><br />
                        <h1>Author notes:</h1>
                        <p>Seava name came from Seavalanche, which is formed by combining the word “sea” and “avalanche”. It was made when I wanted to give name to Betamon in a digimon game. As Betamon has both ice and water element, the combination name fits.</p><br />

                        <p>Since then, I’ve used the name for everything as it’s unique and cool sounding.
                            Seava is technically the second original character I’ve ever created. The first one being Rhon (a blue cat-like creature) featured in Line stickers under cf-seav name in Line Store.</p><br />

                        <p>Seava’s form was inspired by many Pokémon species. The basic idea was to be looking like fennekin, but blue. The Normal form is humanoid, inspired by Zeraora’s body shape. The Ascended form has the cloth hanging behind, inspired by Angewomon from Digimon.</p><br />

                        <p>The color scheme of Seava was chosen to be deep blue (sea), light blue (ice), and cream (sand). The light blue was chosen to be the actual light blue instead of Cerulean Frost (the name that I use in tandem with Seavalanche) for it to look nicely separated from the deep blue.</p><br />
                    </div>
                    <div className='AboutVesnea'>
                        <b>Vesnea</b>
                        <img className='AboutVesneapic' src={AboutVesneapic} alt='D06 - Vesnea Reference' /><br />
                        <p>A fox-like creature that has pinnipeds flippers and tail.
                            She has a cheerful personality, will try to make everyone feels happy.</p>
                        <br /><br />
                        <h1>Author notes:</h1>
                        <p>Vesnea's design was inspired by Vaporeon's body, Brionne's eyes, flippers, and tail, Vulpix's hair, Primarina's hair, Sylveon's color and fangs. Vesnea's design was inspired by Vaporeon's body, Brionne's eyes, flippers, and tail, Vulpix's hair, Primarina's hair, Sylveon's color and fangs.</p><br />

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    )
}

export default About;